{"key":"processedPost-9771193","value":{"id":9771193,"first":9770712,"last":9771583,"when":1234283352,"utime":"02/10/09 06:29 PM","cleanedPost":"I've used all sorts of terrariums with clear and white lids.&nbsp; In fact, the tek on the DVD shows two different terrariums under construction, one with a white lid just to show they work OK.&nbsp; Side light is fine.&nbsp; If it disturbs anyone to see mushrooms growing towards the light, all you have to do is rotate your terrarium every day or two, and they'll balance out.&nbsp; In fact, you can rotate it 90 degrees every day and get spiral mushrooms. <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/laugh.gif\" alt=\":laugh:\" title=\":laugh:\"/><br />RR"}}